      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 98: isDhtProxyCallWakeup() uses substring matching, so values such as \"notAudioCall\" or any future unrelated token containing \"audioCall\"/\"videoCall\" would be treated as call wakeups and keep accounts active for the longer grace period. Since the comment says this field is a comma-separated list of exact values, split and compare exact tokens.\n```suggestion\nprivate fun isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage: RemoteMessage): Boolean {\n    val pushType \u003d remoteMessage.data[\"pt\"] ?: return false\n    return pushType.split(\u0027,\u0027)\n        .map { it.trim() }\n        .any { it \u003d\u003d \"audioCall\" || it \u003d\u003d \"videoCall\" }\n}\n```",
