      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 616: restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() blindly reactivates every recorded account ID without checking whether the account still exists, is still enabled, or still has DHT proxy enabled. If an account is disabled/removed or proxy is turned off while the app is backgrounded, a later push or foreground transition can re-enable it unexpectedly. Re-resolve the account from the current list before restoring and only activate accounts that are still eligible.\n```suggestion\nfor (id in backgroundDeactivatedAccounts) {\n    val account \u003d mAccountList.firstOrNull { it.accountId \u003d\u003d id }\n    if (account?.isEnabled \u003d\u003d true \u0026\u0026 account.isDhtProxyEnabled) {\n        JamiService.setAccountActive(id, true)\n    }\n}\nbackgroundDeactivatedAccounts.clear()\n```",
